## Description {#details}

## Public Member Attributes

### Benefit {#a4d0366572f78a6c014af881252f2f33b}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="unsigned llvm::outliner::Candidate::Benefit = 0">
The number of instructions that would be saved by outlining every candidate of this type.

This is a fixed value which is not updated during the candidate pruning process. It is only used for deciding which candidate to keep if two candidates overlap. The true benefit is stored in the <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/outliner/outlinedfunction">OutlinedFunction</a> for some given candidate.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/machineoutliner-h/#l00198">198</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/machineoutliner-h">MachineOutliner.h</a>.
